firefox.notes: Subscribing to this event does not emit events for all already open browsing contexts.
Before Firefox 140, `clientWindow` was not set on Android.
Firefox emits multiple events when removing a browsingContext with iframes. According to the spec only a single event should be emitted, containing the whole tree of removed contexts.
Before Firefox 140, `clientWindow` was not set on Android.
Before Firefox 101, the parameter was named `parent`.
Before Firefox 129, the `beforeunload` prompt type was not supported.
Only supports `css` and `xpath` locators since Firefox 123, and `accessibility` locators since Firefox 127. Does not yet support `context` and `innerText` locators.

Does not handle navigations that start a download ([bug 1763126](https://bugzil.la/1763126)), to javascript URLs ([bug 1763131](https://bugzil.la/1763131)), or where the initial request never comes back or times out ([bug 1763135](https://bugzil.la/1763135)).
